Converting an odds ratio to a risk difference

Author

TP and RK

Published

November 17, 2023

library(tidyverse)
library(gtsummary)
library(DescTools)

Simulate a genotype g and an outcome y

set.seed(12345)
n <- 10000
minor_allele_freq <- 0.15
genotype <- rbinom(n, 2, minor_allele_freq)
logitp <- -4 + log(1.5)*genotype
p <- plogis(logitp)
y <- rbinom(n, 1, p)
table(y, genotype)
   genotype
y      0    1    2
  0 7090 2480  214
  1  135   69   12

Logistic regression - check simulated OR of ~1.5

logreg <- glm(y ~ genotype, family = binomial)
oddsratio <- exp(coef(logreg)[2])
print(oddsratio)

p0 <- coef(rdreg)[1]
rdiff <- coef(rdreg)[2]
p1 <- rdiff + p0
print(c(p0, p1, rdiff))
(Intercept)    genotype    genotype 
 0.01847777  0.02888771  0.01040994

Formula from Stack Exchange

pt <- (oddsratio * p0)/(1 + (oddsratio * p0) - p0)
print(c(pt, pt - p0, pt / p0))
  genotype   genotype   genotype 
0.02873857 0.01026081 1.55530557

Check OR to RR conversion with DescTools
